snippet.textDisplay:
I'll admit, Endeavor stopped being my most hated character in MHA well before this. But I wasn't expecting my reasons list to include positive ones.
Originally, it was just because Overhaul somehow surpassed Endeavor in child cruelty. But now, Endeavor has been able to acknowledge his past sins and is striving to be a proper #1 Hero. Not just as someone who burns evil to the ground, but as someone who the citizens can feel safe around.
We have seen his growth as a Hero... May Season 5 show us his growth as a Person.

snippet.textDisplay:
This season wasn't just about fights, but it was showing the world without All Might as a Symbol. That even though he is gone, there would still be a Symbol. The Overhaul Arc was strong, showing the growing threats as the world moved on without All Might, but the second half showed not all was lost, that there are people trying to inspire society to never give up. Gentle only wanted to inspire the next generation and Endeavor showed them that the Symbol had not died. Its not the strongest season, but it is still a good one.


Although Season 5 will be extremely better by the second half because the most anticipated arc will be revealed.
